## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Architecture Decision: MongoDB vs PostgreSQL Migration**
> The master plan specifies PostgreSQL. Your current system uses MongoDB. Both are viable paths:
> - **Option A (Recommended):** Keep MongoDB for now, migrate later. This avoids rewrite risk and lets us ship features faster.
> - **Option B:** Migrate to PostgreSQL first. Better for double-entry accounting and relational queries but adds 2-3 weeks.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **AI Infrastructure Decision**
> The master plan calls for local AI models via Ollama (DeepSeek-R1, Qwen2.5, Whisper). This requires significant GPU resources.
> - **Option A (Recommended for dev):** Start with Gemini API (already integrated) for AI features, design agent interfaces to be model-agnostic, swap to local models when GPU is available.
> - **Option B:** Set up Ollama immediately with smaller (1.5B-3B) models for laptop development.

> [!WARNING]
> **Scope Management**
> This is a 22-week plan. Each phase should be treated as a complete deliverable. Do NOT start Phase N+1 until Phase N is verified and stable.

