## Phase 1: Foundation Hardening & Centralized UI System (Weeks 1–3)

> Current sprint. Focus on making existing modules bulletproof + building the scalable UI architecture the user requested.

### UI Architecture Overhaul

#### [NEW] [design-tokens.css](file:///c:/Users/tirth/Desktop/Mini%20project/coreops-erp/frontend/src/styles/design-tokens.css)
- Extract ALL CSS variables from [index.css](file:///c:/Users/tirth/Desktop/Mini%20project/coreops-erp/frontend/src/index.css) into a dedicated design tokens file
- Add semantic token layers: `--color-action-primary`, `--color-surface-*`, `--color-text-*`, `--radius-*`, `--spacing-*`, `--shadow-*`
- Add animation tokens: `--transition-fast`, `--transition-normal`, `--ease-default`

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///c:/Users/tirth/Desktop/Mini%20project/coreops-erp/frontend/src/index.css)
- Import design tokens
- Remove hardcoded values, reference tokens everywhere
- Add utility classes for the design system

#### [MODIFY] UI Components — Centralized Theme System
Every component in `components/ui/` will be updated to:
- Use ONLY CSS variables (zero hardcoded colors)
- Support `variant` and `size` props consistently
- Export prop types for IDE autocomplete

